abstract: Her nomination would offer the best hope of bringing together the party’s warring factions.
snippet: Her nomination would offer the best hope of bringing together the party’s warring factions.
lead_paragraph: Over the weekend, a minor conflict broke out between the presidential campaigns of Bernie Sanders and Elizabeth Warren, longtime friends who have, until now, seemed to operate under an unspoken nonaggression pact.

headline_main: Cory Booker Has More to Say

abstract: We don’t care about Biden’s electability. We want excitement.
snippet: We don’t care about Biden’s electability. We want excitement.
lead_paragraph: KNOXVILLE, Iowa — Welcome to the final Democratic debate before the Iowa caucuses. As a reporter for a small-town Iowa radio station, I have the best seat in the house for the caucuses. I’ve seen all the candidates who have come to Iowa, most multiple times, interviewed nearly all of them, some more than once, and attended countless events. The largest, the Polk County Steak Fry in September, had over 12,000 attendees. The smallest was, um, about 10 people about a week or two ago (sorry, Marianne Williamson!).

headline_print_headline: You Make Iowans Snooze, You Lose

abstract: Ranking first is still the best, of course. But in the Iowa caucuses, second-choice candidates can win.
snippet: Ranking first is still the best, of course. But in the Iowa caucuses, second-choice candidates can win.
lead_paragraph: The snow was starting to come down. Senator Amy Klobuchar was snapping selfies at a campaign event. And Monica Peitz and Peg Raney, two friends from central Iowa, were discussing the question that it seemed every Democrat in the state was asking: Who is on your list?

headline_main: Why Candidates Want to Be Iowans’ Second Choice

abstract: Uncertainty, verging on anxiety and even panic for some Iowa Democrats, reflects the responsibility they feel as they seek a nominee who can beat the president in the general election.
snippet: Uncertainty, verging on anxiety and even panic for some Iowa Democrats, reflects the responsibility they feel as they seek a nominee who can beat the president in the general election.
lead_paragraph: NEWTON, Iowa — Lois Grier knows she has to make a decision about the Democratic primary soon.

abstract: Why are the Monmouth and Selzer results so different? Several possible reasons.
snippet: Why are the Monmouth and Selzer results so different? Several possible reasons.
lead_paragraph: Two of the nation’s best pollsters have recently weighed in on the state of the Iowa Democratic race, with very different results. One subtle methodological choice might explain part of the difference, and on balance there is reason to think Bernie Sanders might be a bit stronger in one of the two polls than the topline result suggested.

headline_main: Recent Poll May Be Underestimating Bernie Sanders’s Strength in Iowa

abstract: Earlier on Monday, Bernie Sanders had denied making the remark in a private 2018 meeting with Elizabeth Warren, accusing her campaign staff of “lying about what happened.”
snippet: Earlier on Monday, Bernie Sanders had denied making the remark in a private 2018 meeting with Elizabeth Warren, accusing her campaign staff of “lying about what happened.”
lead_paragraph: Senator Elizabeth Warren of Massachusetts said on Monday night that Senator Bernie Sanders of Vermont told her in 2018 he did not think a woman could win the presidency. Ms. Warren’s description of the comment, from a private one-on-one meeting, represents a remarkable salvo at her leading liberal rival in the 2020 race just three weeks before the Iowa caucuses.

abstract: The poll, conducted by Monmouth University, found Mr. Biden’s top three competitors in close pursuit.
snippet: The poll, conducted by Monmouth University, found Mr. Biden’s top three competitors in close pursuit.
lead_paragraph: Joseph R. Biden Jr. has regained some of his strength in Iowa, but his three closest rivals for the Democratic nomination remain clustered at his heels, according to a Monmouth University poll released on Monday.

headline_main: New Iowa Poll Shows Tight Race, With Joe Biden Jumping Ahead
headline_print_headline: New Poll Shows a Tight Race in Iowa, With Biden Gaining Momentum

abstract: The New Jersey senator, who built his campaign around a message of unity, was unable to catch on with substantial numbers of voters and ended his quest before voting began.
snippet: The New Jersey senator, who built his campaign around a message of unity, was unable to catch on with substantial numbers of voters and ended his quest before voting began.
lead_paragraph: For almost two decades, Senator Cory Booker of New Jersey has been viewed as a future leader in the Democratic Party, a former Rhodes scholar and Stanford football player who achieved national prominence as mayor of Newark.
